Diagnosis . Dorsal surface of head with two deep, oval pits connected by arcuate groove (
Figs. 2, 4
); genal projections obsolete; antenna long, with antennomeres III and XI elongate, club longer and rather loose (
Fig. 3
); male fore tarsi distinctly expanded.

